article.description: North Dakota State beats Oral Roberts 72-66 in Summit opener
article.headline: North Dakota State beats Oral Roberts 72-66 in Summit opener
article.linkText: North Dakota State beats Oral Roberts 72-66 in Summit opener
article.story: FARGO, N.D. -- Lawrence Alexander scored a career-high 31 points, including 6 of 10 3-pointers, and North Dakota State beat Oral Roberts 72-66 with a late surge on Friday in a Summit League opener. Tied at halftime, Lawrence scored the go-ahead free throw, 67-66, with 42 seconds left to spark an 8-0 run and the Bison (9-5, 1-0) pulled away. Dexter Werner scored 13 and the Bison shot 11 of 22 from distance. The Bison led 21-6 after free throws by Alexander, but Oral Roberts rallied 21-3 to lead 34-29. The Bison used a 5-0 run to tie it at 34 at halftime. Oral Roberts led 41-36 on a 3-pointer by Obi Emegano early in the second half, but Alexander hit back-to-back 3s and the Bison led 42-41. The lead traded hands nine more times before Alexander's go-ahead free throw. Emegano scored 25 for Oral Roberts (6-8, 0-1), Henderson had 17 and Korey Billbury 13.
